TI  - Chest wall injury surgeon, know thyself.
PG  - 18-19
LID - 10.1097/TA.0000000000004723 [doi]
AB  - The use of surgical stabilization of rib fractures (SSRF) for non-flail fracture 
      patterns continues to rise. However, multiple, recent randomized controlled 
      trials in this patient population have failed to show a clear benefit to surgery. 
      Rather than widening the gap between research and practice, we must embrace these 
      trials, learn from them, and continue to refine the indications for surgery. 
      Approaching SSRF with an awareness of our own cognitive biases, as well as 
      scientific rigor, will advance the discipline of chest wall injury surgery.
